<br>
The experience itself is perfect too.  It's not elemental planes, nor is it Plane of Valor/Bastion of Thunder.  I see just enough improvement in my experience bar to make it all worthwhile.  In the end, I forget I'm even getting experience and it's actually a pleasant surprise to see my exp bar has jumped as much as it has.  If I want AA, fast, I go do BoT or the e-planes, but after this, I won't be daily grinding there anymore.<br>
<br>
Caillou, seriously.  You haven't even been in a dungeon yet, right?  So why are you complaining?  Infact, why is anyone complaining about unpacifyable mobs or aggro ranges or anything like that?<br>
<br>
These encounters are dungeon crawls.  They are not exp camps.  They are not boring-set-up-a-camp-lets-go-grind encounters.  They are designed to kill you.  You need your wits about you.  They are not controllable camps.  You take a chance.  If you decide to investigate too far, there is a chance they will hit you with something nasty.  I wasn't swearing at my screen when I put a bitten victim to rest and found three spiders jumped out of the corpse.  Instead, it made me wary of the next time it happened.  I was so impressed at what they had done and damn it, it gave the place atmosphere!  No back spawns meant not only was I wary of what might come behind, and it also made CR easier.  It ALSO means that you don't need a wizard/druid/graveyard to exit the place.<br>
<br>
You die in dungeon crawls.  It's the reality of it.  Sometimes you get hit hard, sometimes you don't.  I'd rather die laughing, knowing I was killed by the dungeon after a supremely hard fight than spend six friggin hours in BoT at exp_camp_01.<br>
<br>
It should also be noted that there are many other unused zones similar to these that while they may be less scripted, they are also suitable for dungeon crawls and not similarly level restricted.<br>
<br>
The raids however seem to be designed for elemental guilds and plane of time guilds.  I'm not sure, we'll find out soon enough.<br>
<br>
I'm with Tinwin.  You've all gone soft <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Look beyond the restrictions, grab an aligned group if you want, and smash through the place.  Three paladins, a cleric, a wizard and a bard can tear up Mistmoore.  The only thing I recommend you do is take along haste.  Haste more than anything.<br>
<br>
The beta testers were dead wrong about this one.  I personally think they just wanted to complain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roninsenshi>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia<br>Jihad on that ass!</span><br>  Posts: 2253<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/11/03 9:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4005.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: LDoN Level Restrictions</span><hr size=1> The Beta testers forgot one thing.<br>
