<br>
My first LDoN dungeon consisted of two level 65s, two 62s, one 61, and one 59.  Average group level was 62 1/3.  We completed the dungeon with 45 minutes left to spare.  Everything we fought was DB to me and my mana bar never got below 80%.  I only nuked once per fight because the mobs would be almost dead before I could get a second nuke off.  <br>
<br>
On the second dungeon, a level 65 replaced the level 59. So the average group level went up to 63 1/3 (+1).  Mobs were still DB but they hit a helluva lot harder and I ended up nuking 2-3 times a fight before it was dead.  My baby woke up so I had to gate out and camp.  This caused the group to fail the adventure because they couldn't add someone to replace me.  Had I been able to stay, we had a decent chance of winning.  But it would have taken a lot longer than the 45 minutes it took us to win the first dungeon.<br>
<br>
If the original grouping rules were in effect, folks would add lower level characters to the group in order to lower the group average level, which in turn would make the dungeons too easy.   So I congratulate SOE for having the foresight to have a system in place that prevents that. <p>Kebkin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
